%******************************************************************************************************************************%
%****************************************************** `my-patches.sty' ******************************************************%
%******************************************************************************************************************************%
% Provides a single package for loading/applying each of the patches in 'my-latex' to the corresponding packages, with each patch 'my-X-patch' modifying a subset of the macros/commands/environments of a package 'X' and providing centralized control (typically from 'my-definitions') over their content's behavior/appearance through a set of register variables and/or control sequences.  A set of corresponding register variables and control sequences are also created and coupled to those of each (sub)package generating content of a particular type/category (e.g., 'tcolorbox'/'tikz' environments, front/back matter, etc.), thereby ensuring the content generated by (sub)packages of a particular type/category maintain consistent behavior/appearance by automatically propagating modifications of these type/category specific definitions to each of the corresponding (sub)packages.  To prevent errors/clashes in existing documents, the adapted versions of packages like 'glossaries', 'nomencl', and 'imakeidx' with hard-coded modifications will be redesigned as "package + patch" implementations and macro/command/environment modifications will be redefined as needed to ensure support for their original syntax/usage.  Additional 'my-latex' package options will also be included to provide users with the option to exclude specific patches and instead use the base package so they can incorporate some aspect of 'my-latex' into their documents while preserving the original behavior/appearance of content generated by one of the base packages.  It is also possible to control the behavior/appearance of the content generated by a particular (sub)package by decoupling the corresponding register variable(s) and/or control sequence(s) from those of the entire type/category, but there is currently no mechanism to restore this coupling.  This deficiency is relatively easy to resolve (all be it time consuming) and will likely involve permanent coupling but allowing this to be overridden based on Boolean/optional arguments provided by 'xparse'.
%
% Note that this package does not include patches that must be applied immediately after loading the underlying base package.  In such cases the loading of the base package 'X' and immediate application of the patch (either by inserting the corresponding code explicitly or loading the subpackage 'my-X-patch' containing it) are encapsulated in a new package 'X-patched', thereby guaranteeing these 2 steps occur sequentially by loading 'X-patched' in place of the base package.
%******************************************************************************************************************************%
%*************************************** Define provided package name and LaTeX/package dependencies *************************************%
%******************************************************************************************************************************%
\NeedsTeXFormat{LaTeX2e}[2005/12/01]
\ProvidesPackage{my-patches}                    % Provides patches w/ modified/additional register variables/macros/commands/environments
\RequirePackage{my-shadowtext-patch}            % Patch of `shadowtext` package, removing spaces preceding shadowed text
\RequirePackage{my-cool-patch}                  % Patch of `cool` package, applying '\scriptscriptstyle' to exponents to reduce font size
%******************************************************************************************************************************%
%****************************************** Package options and corresponding Boolean variables ******************************************%
%******************************************************************************************************************************%
%------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------%
\DeclareOption*{\PackageWarning{my-patches}{Unknown \CurrentOption}}
